definitions.definition: To make a sound resembling such a cry.
examples: The jet engines whined at take off.

definitions.definition: To complain or protest with a whine (compare whinge ) or as if with a whine.
To move with a whining sound.
examples: The jet whined into the air.
The wind whined and moaned through the trees.

definitions.definition: To utter with the sound of a whine.
examples: The child whined all his complaints.
Kelly Queen was whining that the boss made him put on his tie.

main_definition: ( intransitive ) To utter a high-pitched cry.
secondary_definitions: ( intransitive ) To make a sound resembling such a cry.
( intransitive ) To complain or protest with a whine (compare whinge ) or as if with a whine.
( intransitive ) To move with a whining sound.
( transitive ) To utter with the sound of a whine.
